          %h3 Riot points
          %p
            RP is an alternative currency to the earned IP (influence points). It can be used to purchase anything except runes, and skins can only be purchased with RP. You start out with 400 RP but cannot earn any more in game. Usually you have to spend money to get more RP but there are two other methods to acquire RP.
          %p
            The first is to sign up for the free Bing rewards program and search with Bing instead of Google. You can use earned points to purchase a $5 Burger King gift card, which can then be redeemed for Riot Points in the client. Here is
            %a{href: "http://www.bing.com/explore/rewards?PUBL=REFERAFRIEND&CREA=RAW&rrid=_d6ea93ad-711b-b795-cdc9-bb4bd0c0b210"} my referral link
            to sign up
            %i.fa.fa-heart-o 

          %p
            The second method is to
            %a{href: "https://www.serve.com/leagueoflegends/"} sign up for the American Express Serve RP+ card.
            This is also free to do, and as a prepaid card does NOT affect your credit. However, you should be aware of 
            %a{href: "https://m.serve.com/fee-chart/"} monthly fees
            (which can be waived). It is pretty easy to get 13,000 RP with this.


